-- MOVES-FM Global promotes two vice-presidents 
-- 
-- Mon Sep 15, 2014 01:39PM EDT
-- None



Sept 15 (Reuters) - FM Global, a commercial and industrial property insurer, promoted two of its senior employees, effective Oct. 1.

Chris Johnson will now oversee FM Global's international operations and Affiliated FM, a division that specializes in mid-market property insurance. He will be based in the company's corporate office in Johnston, Rhode Island. Johnson was previously a senior vice president and the company's EMEA division manager. Vincent Reyda will take over Johnson's previous duties and will be based in the company's Windsor, UK office.